The steps followed:

Git & GitHub Exercise
Project: EmployeeProject
Objective
Learn how to:
•	Create a project folder 
•	Initialize Git 
•	Connect with GitHub 
•	Push code 
•	Make changes and track versions 

Exercise 1: Create Project Folder
Step 1: Create a folder
Go to C:\ drive and create a folder named:
C:\EmployeeProject
Step 2: Open Command Prompt / VS Code Terminal
Navigate to the folder:
cd C:\EmployeeProject
Explanation:
•	cd means change directory 
•	This tells the system: “Work inside this folder” 

Exercise 2: Initialize Git
Step 3: Initialize Git repository
git init
Explanation:
•	This creates a hidden .git folder 
•	Git starts tracking your project 

Exercise 3: Create First File
Step 4: Create a file
Create a file named:
employee.txt
Add content:
Employee Project
Name: John
Role: Developer

Exercise 4: Check Git Status
Step 5: Check file status
git status
Explanation:
•	Shows: 
o	Untracked files 
o	Modified files 
•	Currently, employee.txt is untracked 

Exercise 5: Add File to Git
Step 6: Add file
git add employee.txt
OR add all files:
git add .
Explanation:
•	Moves file to staging area 
•	Git is ready to save it 

Exercise 6: Commit Changes
Step 7: Commit
git commit -m "First commit - added employee file"
Explanation:
•	A commit = snapshot of your project 
•	-m adds a message explaining changes 

Exercise 7: Connect to GitHub
Step 8: Add remote repository
git remote add origin https://github.com/monicag-gupta/EmployeeProject
Explanation:
•	Connects local project to GitHub 
•	origin = name of remote repository 

Exercise 8: Push Code to GitHub
Step 9: Push code
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
Explanation:
•	branch -M main → sets branch name 
•	push → uploads code to GitHub 
•	-u → links local and remote branch 

Exercise 9: Make Changes
Step 10: Update file
Edit employee.txt:
Employee Project
Name: John
Role: Senior Developer

Step 11: Check changes
git status

Step 12: View differences
git diff
Explanation:
•	Shows what changed in the file 

Exercise 10: Commit Updated Code
Step 13: Add and commit
git add .
git commit -m "Updated employee role"

Step 14: Push again
git push

Exercise 11: Create New Branch
Step 15: Create branch
git checkout -b feature-update
Explanation:
•	Creates a new branch for changes 
•	Keeps main code safe 

Step 16: Make changes in branch
Add:
Department: IT

Step 17: Commit changes
git add .
git commit -m "Added department"

Exercise 12: Merge Branch
Step 18: Switch to main
git checkout main

Step 19: Merge branch
git merge feature-update
Explanation:
•	Combines branch changes into main 

Exercise 13: View History
Step 20: Check log
git log
Explanation:
•	Shows all commits history 

Exercise 14: Clone Repository
Step 21: Clone project elsewhere
cd C:\
git clone https://github.com/monicag-gupta/EmployeeProject
Explanation:
•	Downloads project from GitHub 
•	Useful for teamwork 

